SIMPLE: defunct
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Defunct
<hw>De*funct"</hw> <pr>(d⟦esl⟧*f⟦ucr⟧⟦nsm⟧kt")</pr>. <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>defunctus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>defungi</ets> to acquit
one's self of, to perform, finish, depart, die; <ets>de</ets> +
<ets>fungi</ets> to perform, discharge: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧funt</ets>.
See <er>Function</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having finished the
course of life; dead; deceased.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Defunct</xex>
organs.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The boar, <qex>defunct</qex>, lay tripped up, near.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>No longer in effect or use; no longer operating;
<as>as, a <ex>defunct</ex> business; a <ex>defunct</ex>
law</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defunct</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Defunct
<hw>De*funct"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dead person; one
deceased.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defunction</ent>⟦br⟧
